          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gaussians were Fitted to the Proton Peak For",
                " Each Angular Bin. Since the Data Only Span a Part of",
                " The Full Angular Range, It was Extrapolated by Using",
                " Several Phase Shift Solutions. In this Way the",
                " Differential Data Could be Integrated and Normalized",
                " To the Total Cross Section."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The Neutrons Showed a Semi-Monoenergetic Neutron Spec-",
                " Trum, with a Full Energy Peak at 162+/-1 MeV and a",
                " Low-Energy Tail. The Latter was Supressed by Tof",
                " Techniques. The Energy Resolution of the Main Peak",
                " Was 1.3 and 2.3 MeV Fwhm For the Thin and Thick",
                " Targets, Respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Errors Given are a Combination of",
                " Statistical and Systematic Uncertainties, and",
                " Originate from Counting Statistics, the Peak-Fitting",
                " Procedure and 12-C Background Subtraction. In Addi-",
                " Tion, There is a Systematic Uncertainty Between the",
                " First and the Fifth Data Set of +/-2.6 Per-Cent, and",
                " A Cross Section Scale Uncertainty of +/-2.3 Per-Cent."
              ]
            }
          ],
